{
  "topicId": "m4-t1",
  "title": "Talking About Money and Asking for Prices",
  "dialect": "fusha",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Money: نقود",
          "arabic": "النقود"
        },
        "text": "The most general term for money in Arabic is 'نقود'. It is a plural noun, but often used to refer to money in general. You will hear this word often in everyday situations.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أحتاجُ نُقوداً.",
            "english": "I need money.",
            "transliteration": "Ahṭāju nuqūdan."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هل لديكَ نُقود؟",
            "english": "Do you (m) have money?",
            "transliteration": "Hal ladayka nuqūd?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Currency: عملة",
          "arabic": "العملة"
        },
        "text": "When you want to refer to a specific type of money, like a dollar, euro, or dinar, the term 'عملة' is used. It means 'currency'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "ما هيَ عُملةُ بلدكَ؟",
            "english": "What is your country's currency?",
            "transliteration": "Mā hiya 'umlatu baladika?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هذهِ عُملةٌ نادرة.",
            "english": "This is a rare currency.",
            "transliteration": "Hādhihi 'umlatun nādirah."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How Much?': كم الثمن؟ / بكم؟",
          "arabic": "كم الثمن؟ / بكم؟"
        },
        "text": "These are the two most common ways to ask 'How much is it?' or 'What is the price?' 'كم الثمن؟' literally means 'How much is the price?' while 'بكم؟' means 'For how much?'. Both are widely understood.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "كم الثمن؟",
            "english": "How much is it?",
            "transliteration": "Kam ath-thaman?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "بكم هذا؟",
            "english": "How much is this (m)?",
            "transliteration": "Bikam hādhā?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "أحتاجُ نُقوداً لأشتري عُملة.",
        "english": "I need money to buy currency.",
        "transliteration": "Ahṭāju nuqūdan li-ashtarī 'umlah."
      },
      "context": "Combining 'money' and 'currency' with the verb 'to buy'."
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "بكم هذهِ العُملة؟",
        "english": "How much is this currency?",
        "transliteration": "Bikam hādhihi al-'umlah?"
      },
      "context": "Asking the price of a specific currency."
    },
    {
