    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "The Dinar: دينار",
          "arabic": "الدينار"
        },
        "text": "The Dinar is a common currency unit in several Arab countries, including Kuwait, Bahrain, Jordan, Iraq, and Algeria. It is a masculine noun.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "هذا دينارٌ كويتيٌّ.",
            "english": "This is a Kuwaiti Dinar.",
            "transliteration": "Hādhā dīnārun kuwaytīyun."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أريدُ عشرةَ دنانير.",
            "english": "I want ten Dinars.",
            "transliteration": "Urīdu 'asharata danānīr."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "The Dirham: درهم",
          "arabic": "الدرهم"
        },
        "text": "The Dirham is the currency used in countries like the United Arab Emirates (UAE) and Morocco. It is also a masculine noun.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "كم سعرُ هذا بالدرهم؟",
            "english": "How much is this (m) in Dirhams?",
            "transliteration": "Kam si'ru hādhā bid-dirham?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "معي خمسةُ دراهم.",
            "english": "I have five Dirhams.",
            "transliteration": "Ma'ī khamsatu darāhim."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "The Riyal: ريال",
          "arabic": "الريال"
        },
        "text": "The Riyal is the official currency in Saudi Arabia, Qatar, and Yemen. It is a masculine noun.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "هذا يُكلّفُ مئةَ ريال.",
            "english": "This costs one hundred Riyals.",
            "transliteration": "Hādhā yukallifu mi'ata riyāl."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هل تقبلُ الريالَ السعوديَّ؟",
            "english": "Do you accept Saudi Riyals?",
            "transliteration": "Hal taqbalu ar-riyāla as-sa'ūdiyya?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
