    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Numbers for Prices (1-10)",
          "arabic": "الأرقام للأسعار (١-١٠)"
        },
        "text": "Understanding basic numbers is crucial for prices. Here are 'one', 'two', and 'ten' as examples. Remember that numbers agree in gender with the noun they quantify (for numbers 3-10, it's inverse agreement).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "واحد",
            "english": "one (m)",
            "transliteration": "Wāḥid"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "اثنان",
            "english": "two (m)",
            "transliteration": "Ithnān"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "عشرة",
            "english": "ten (m)",
            "transliteration": "'Asharah"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "I want: أريدُ",
          "arabic": "أريدُ"
        },
        "text": "The verb 'أريدُ' means 'I want'. It is essential for expressing your desire to purchase something. It is followed by the object you want, or by 'أنْ' (an) + a verb in the subjunctive mood.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أريدُ هذا.",
            "english": "I want this.",
            "transliteration": "Urīdu hādhā."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أريدُ ماءً.",
            "english": "I want water.",
            "transliteration": "Urīdu mā'an."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Price: سعر",
          "arabic": "السعر"
        },
        "text": "Another term for 'price' is 'سعر'. You can use it interchangeably with 'ثمن' (thaman) in many contexts when asking about costs.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "ما هوَ سِعرُ التفاح؟",
            "english": "What is the price of the apples?",
            "transliteration": "Mā huwa si'ru at-tuffāḥ?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "السِّعرُ جيد.",
            "english": "The price is good.",
            "transliteration": "As-si'ru jayyid."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "أريدُ هذا، كم سعرهُ؟",
        "english": "I want this, what is its price?",
        "transliteration": "Urīdu hādhā, kam si'ruhu?"
      },
      "context": "Combining 'I want' with asking the price of an item."
    },
