    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expensive: غالٍ",
          "arabic": "غالٍ"
        },
        "text": "To describe something as expensive, you use the adjective 'غالٍ'. Note that in its indefinite form, the 'ي' at the end is often omitted in writing, indicated by two kasra marks (tanwīn al-kasr) under the 'ل'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "هذا غالٍ جداً.",
            "english": "This is very expensive.",
            "transliteration": "Hādhā ghālin jiddan."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "السِّعرُ غالٍ.",
            "english": "The price is expensive.",
            "transliteration": "As-si'ru ghālin."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Cheap: رخيص",
          "arabic": "رخيص"
        },
        "text": "The opposite of expensive is 'رخيص', meaning 'cheap' or 'inexpensive'. This is a common adjective to describe prices or items.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "هذا رخيصٌ.",
            "english": "This is cheap.",
            "transliteration": "Hādhā rakhīṣun."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "السِّعرُ رخيص.",
            "english": "The price is cheap.",
            "transliteration": "As-si'ru rakhīṣ."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Can you reduce the price?: هل يمكنكَ تخفيض السِّعر؟",
